2 Section 2. Section 77-3-502, MCA, is amended to read:
3 "77-3-502. Rules. (1) The Subject to the Enabling Act, constitutional restrictions, and state law, the
4 board shall have has the power and authority to prescribe such rules and to do and perform all acts and things
5 not inconsistent with The Enabling Act, the constitution, and the statutes of this state as it may deem necessary
6 and proper relating to the leasing of state lands for the underground storage of natural gas or liquified gas and
7 the sale of the gas remaining in state lands in a gas field wherein in which native gas deposits have been
8 depleted.
9 (2) The board may exercise its authority to prescribe rules more stringent than federal regulations
10 or guidelines to protect drinking water sources pursuant to the federal Safe Drinking Water Act, 42 U.S.C. 300f,
11 et seq."
12
13 Section 3. Section 77-3-505, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "77-3-505. Bond of lessees. A lessee under 77-3-501 shall furnish bond to the state in a form
15 prescribed by the board and in an amount adequate to indemnify the state against loss, damage, or detriment
16 by reason of failure of the lessee to fully discharge the obligations contained in any lease. No A bond in excess
17 of not less than $20,000 is may not be is required under any one lease for the storage of gas or liquified gas."
18
19 Section 4. Section 77-3-507, MCA, is amended to read:
20 "77-3-507. Lessee to prevent waste. (1) Leases All leases issued under the provisions of this part
21 shall all be are subject to the conditions that the lessee in conducting the underground storage of natural gas or
22 liquified gas shall use all reasonable precautions to prevent waste of oil or gas developed in the land or the
23 entrance of water, through wells drilled to store natural gas or liquified gas, to the oil or gas sands or oil or gas
24 bearing to oil-bearing or gas-bearing strata to the destruction or injury of oil or gas deposits.
25 (2) Violations A violation of any of these conditions shall constitute is grounds for the forfeiture of
26 the lease after a hearing had thereon on the violation before the board."
27 - END -
